Date: Sun18 Jul 2004
From: Thomas M Yuill <tmyuill@facstaff.wisc.edu>

A Comment on Risk Awareness
---------------------------
Wildlife biologists need to become aware of the risks of being exposed to
hantaviruses from handling small rodents, and the relatively simple,
inexpensive preventive measures that can be taken to reduce that risk. An
educational program ought to be carried by the Wildlife Society and its
local chapters and similar professional groups to inform its members.
--
Tom Yuill
Professor and Director Emeritus
University of Wisconsin-Madison
<tmyuill@facstaff.wisc.edu>
